10/01/81	booktitle.compin

Syntax:  .ifi booktitle "title" orderno {punctuation}


Function:
This macro formats a citation of a published manual.


Macro action:
1) formats the manual citation according to HIS Publication Standards,
   setting the 'title' in Century Schoolbook Medium Italic, followed by
   a comma and "(Order No.  'orderno')" in Century Schoolbok Roman,
   followed by the optional 'punctuation'.


NOTES:
1) If "title" contains white space, it must be given as a quoted
   string.
2) 'punctuation' is normally "."  or ",", but may be any other string
   of the users choice.
